HEADWORD: Straitness
<hw>Strait"ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality or condition of
being strait; especially, a pinched condition or situation caused by
poverty; <as>as, the <ex>straitness</ex>of their
circumstances</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Strait-waistcoat</ent>⟦br⟧
